    .custom-guidelines {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        background-color: ;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
    }

    .custom-guidelines .container {
        width: 80%;
        margin: 30px auto;
        background-color: #fffaf0;
        padding: 20px;
        border-radius: 8px;
        box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    }

    .custom-guidelines h1 {
        text-align: center;
        color: #e74c3c; /* Red color for title */
    }

    .custom-guidelines p {
        font-size: 16px;
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: #2C3E50;
    }

    .custom-guidelines h2 {
        color: #2980B9;
        font-size: 22px;
        margin-top: 20px;
    }

    .custom-guidelines ul {
        list-style-type: none;
        padding: 0;
    }

    .custom-guidelines li {
        background-color: #ecf0f1;
        margin: 10px 0;
        padding: 15px;
        border-radius: 5px;
    }

    .custom-guidelines li:hover {
        background-color: #d6dbdf;
    }

    .custom-guidelines li::before {
        content: "✔";
        color: #27ae60;
        font-weight: bold;
        display: inline-block;
        width: 20px;
    }

    @media screen and (max-width: 768px) {
        .custom-guidelines .container {
            width: 95%;
        }

        .custom-guidelines h1 {
            font-size: 24px;
        }

        .custom-guidelines p, .custom-guidelines h2 {
            font-size: 18px;
        }
    }
</style>

<div class="custom-guidelines">
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Abstract Submission Guidelines</h1>
        <p><b>Student Presentations:</b> 2 November 10:10-14:55</p>
        <p><b>Abstract Submission Deadline:</b> 25 September 23:59</p>
        <p>When submitting an abstract for the symposium, it is essential to follow the specified instructions to ensure your submission is considered. Here are the guidelines to help you prepare:</p>

        <ul>
            <li><b>Scope and Relevance:</b> Submissions must align with topics in bioinformatics or computational biology. Unpublished work is preferred, but previously published work is also accepted (provided it has not been submitted to RSG-Türkiye Symposiums before).</li>

            <li><b>Evaluation Criteria:</b> Submissions will be evaluated based on the following:
                <ul>
                    <li><b>Clarity:</b> The research is clearly presented and easy to understand.</li>
                    <li><b>Originality:</b> The work offers new insights or findings.</li>
                    <li><b>Relevance:</b> The topic fits well within the symposium’s focus.</li>
                    <li><b>Scientific Quality:</b> The results are meaningful and valuable.</li>
                    <li><b>Completeness:</b> The abstract covers all critical aspects of the research.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>

            <li><b>Abstract Formatting:</b>
                <ul>
                    <li><b>Title:</b> Should be concise yet descriptive of the research.</li>
                    <li><b>Word Limit:</b> The abstract must not exceed 200 words.</li>
                    <li><b>Structure:</b> Use the following sections:
                        <ul>
                            <li><b>Background:</b> Provide context and state the purpose of your study.</li>
                            <li><b>Methodology:</b> Briefly describe the methods used.</li>
                            <li><b>Results:</b> Highlight key findings.</li>
                            <li><b>Conclusions:</b> Summarize the significance and potential impact.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>

            <li><b>Author and Submission Rules:</b> No personal information (e.g., affiliations or titles) should be included in the abstract. This data will be collected separately via the submission platform. Co-authors are allowed, but only the presenting author will receive the presentation or award certificate. All authors' names will appear in the conference abstract book. A participant can present only one submission (even if they are co-author on multiple works). The presenting author must be actively involved in the research presented.</li>

            <li><b>Presentation Formats:</b> Submitters can choose between the following presentation options:
                <ul>
                    <li><b>Oral only</b></li>
                    <li><b>Oral or poster:</b> The abstract will first be considered for an oral presentation. If not selected for oral presentation, it will automatically be reviewed for a poster presentation.</li>
                    <li><b>Poster only</b></li>
                </ul>
            </li>

            <li><b>Additional Notes:</b> Avoid using abbreviations or references in the abstract. All accepted abstracts will be published in the symposium proceedings.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>For any other queries, please write to us at <a href="mailto:rsg-turkey@iscbsc.org">rsg-turkey@iscbsc.org</a></p>

        <p>We look forward to receiving your submissions and seeing your valuable contributions at the symposium. Good luck with your abstract!</p>
    </div>
</div>
